comments: Ball (CHA) briefly places a hand/arm to the front of Murray (SAS) during the drive and the marginal contact does not affects his SQBR.
Murray (SAS) extends his leg as Ball (CHA) closes out. The contact is marginal.
Ball (CHA) legally contests Johnson's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Murray (SAS) makes contact to Ball's (CHA) body on the drive that affects his SQBR.
Bridges (CHA) makes marginal contact with Murray's (SAS) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Vassell (SAS) firms up and absorbs the contact.
Primo (SAS) makes contact with Martin's (CHA) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Murray (SAS) does not lift his foot from the floor as he turns on his foot.
Plumlee (CHA) legally contests Johnson's (SAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Poeltl (SAS) makes contact to Martin's (CHA) arm as he gains control of the rebound.
